content.description: Climber the off-vertical face from left-facing side pulls.  Top out straight up with high-step.
content.location: Go to Forest Area of The Beach in Tumwater Canyon. Walk in and the big boulder in the middle is The Warmup boulder. As you walk up to the boulder, the route is right in front of you, a bit to the left on the slightly spoon-like face.

content.description: Climb the short face on right of The Warmup boulder. Multiple variations possible.
content.location: Go to Forest Area of The Beach in Tumwater Canyon. Walk in and the big boulder in the middle is The Warmup boulder. As you walk up to the boulder there will be a corner, go about eight feet around to the right and the short, frequently dirty face is the start.

content.description: Start crouched on corner with chest-high slopers, then slap up and right to incuts, top out straight up.
content.location: Go to Forest Area of The Beach in Tumwater Canyon. Walk in and the big boulder in the middle is The Warmup boulder. As you walk up to the boulder, the route starts on the obvious corner.

content.description: Climb the short slab on the back of The Warmup boulder. There is a left and right variation with the option to not use the arêtes.
content.location: The Beach - Forest Area.  The Warmup boulder is in the middle of it all, just walk around to the backside.

content.description: Start on a sloper on the left arête of the The Warmup boulder.  Mantle, walk up the slab, and finish on better holds up and a little right.
content.location: Go to Forest Area of The Beach in Tumwater Canyon. Walk in and the big boulder in the middle is The Warmup boulder. As you walk up to the boulder go around left and before the tree is the start.
